Package: ebrecipe
Type: Package
Title: Log-Spline Empirical Bayes Deconvolution, Shrinkage, and Selection
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
        "JoonHo", "Lee",
        email = "jlee296@ua.edu",
        role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
    )
Description: Implements the three-step empirical Bayes (EB) recipe ---
    estimate, denoise, decide --- described in Walters (2024, Handbook of
    Labor Economics, Elsevier), with a log-spline deconvolution engine
    applicable to any domain where noisy unit-level estimates require
    shrinkage. Provides a release-candidate logspline EB workflow for
    unit-level estimation input, precision-dependence diagnostics,
    Walters-style standardization, log-spline prior deconvolution,
    posterior shrinkage, false discovery rate control, and decision-rule
    comparison. Includes both a one-function interface for quick analyses
    and a composable step-by-step pipeline for advanced workflows, plus a
    linear school value-added workflow and bundled datasets for the
    discrimination and simulated VAM examples discussed in Walters (2024).
    Some optional backend bridges and advanced controls remain intentionally
    narrow at this checkpoint.
